General Motors Corp said it plans tooffer driver-side airbags as standard equipment on 500,000  cars in the 1990 model year and up to three mln by 1992 if afederal safety rule is relaxed for domestic automakers.    A GM spokesman said the statement comes in advance of acongressional hearing tomorrow in Washington on a proposedextension of a federal deadline for installation of "automaticoccupant protection systems" on all cars beyond the currentSeptember, 1989, target.    GM previously said it would offer airbags as optionalequipment on its 1988-model Oldsmobile Delta 88 models.    Reuter&#3;